Introduction

GENBLUE is a Taiwanese girl group under TEN Entertainment, formed through the reality survival show NEXTGIRLZ. The group consists of six members: XXIN, Ayeon, Hsu Yuan Yuan, Yu, Ayako, and Nico. Rong Rong, Bido, and Vicky left the group before their official debut.

On September 2, 2024, GENBLUE made their debut in Korea with the single "COCOCO."

The name "GENBLUE" is derived from the blue crystal, symbolizing courage, and reflects the group's Generation Z spirit and attitude.
